==English==
'''question'''
===Noun===

1 - a sentence, phrase or word which asks for [[information]], that asks for a reply or response
:"he asked a direct question";
:'''Synonyms''' - [[inquiry]], [[enquiry]], [[query]]

2 - a subject/topic under consideration/discussion; 
:"the question of seniority will be discussed at the meeting";
:'''Synonyms''' - [[subject]], [[topic]], [[problem]], [[issue]]

3 - a period or moment of questioning; 
:"there was a question about which material to use";
:'''Synonyms''' - [[consideration]], [[inquiry]]

4 - doubt or challenge about the truth or accuracy of a matter; 
:"there is a question over his claim to the property";
:'''Synonyms''' - [[doubt]]

5 - a formal proposal to a meeting as a topic for discussion and vote; 
:"I move that the question be put to the vote";
:'''Synonyms''' - [[motion]], [[proposition]], [[proposal]]

6 - "pop the question" - "to make a marriage proposal" - ''usage - informal, jocular''

